<item>
            <title>[SPR-2468] Double escaping in form:input and form:textarea tags</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2468</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I seem to be getting a double escaping issue where my form tags are escaping the ampersand from escaped entities like so:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;input id=&quot;name&quot; name=&quot;name&quot; type=&quot;text&quot; value=&quot;&amp;amp;quot;The Park&amp;amp;quot; - Martin Luther King Jr. Civic Center Park&quot; size=&quot;40&quot; maxlength=&quot;100&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so that what appears as the value of the form field is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;The Park&amp;quot; - Martin Luther King Jr. Civic Center Park&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;instead of:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The Park&quot; - Martin Luther King Jr. Civic Center Park&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have &quot;defaultHtmlEscape&quot; set in web.xml &amp;#8211; I simply set &quot;htmlEscape&quot; to true in the tags. If I do set &quot;defaultHtmlEscape&quot; I get the same problem. If no escaping is turned on, the double quotes are directly written to the page and the tag breaks:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;input id=&quot;name&quot; name=&quot;name&quot; type=&quot;text&quot; value=&quot;&quot;The Park&quot; - Martin Luther King Jr. Civic Center Park&quot; size=&quot;40&quot; maxlength=&quot;100&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Has anyone else encountered this? So far I love the form tags, but this is a show stopper for me.  I have a thread open in the forums:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=28343&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=28343&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but nobody seems to be responding.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
