                            <comment id="19186" author="dhalbrook" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2006 07:23:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I forgot to note that the original data does NOT contain entities.  The original data is:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;The Park&quot; - Martin Luther King Jr. Civic Center Park &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19217" author="rpaul" created="Fri, 25 Aug 2006 16:45:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Experiencing the same problem here.  I was using defaultHtmlEscape and all my input:text and input:textarea inputs where receiving the double escape treatment.  I don&apos;t think htmlEscape is required for input:textarea as the content is not an attribute of the input element. i.e.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;input type=&quot;textarea&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   content goes here&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/input&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
However for input:text it is quite a pain having to convert to writing manual input elements as a workaround for this bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19508" author="springboy" created="Sun, 10 Sep 2006 05:53:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HTML escaping was being performed in two places in the codebase (hence the bug), and now HTML escaping is performed by one class only (ValueFormatter).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
